 <p>
  <em>
   MSFS 2024
  </em>
  ’s Career Mode progression is tied to three currencies: Credit (money), EXP (skill), and Reputation (status).
 </p>
 <!-- No repeatable ad for zone: character count repeatable. -->
 <!-- Repeatable debug data: {"injection":"none","adPosition":4,"startingPoint":0,"skipEvery":null,"nbrPlacementFilledEachSkip":4,"nbrPlacementsScanned":4,"ruleCount":1000,"degradationStartingPoint":1,"stopAds":null,"actualCount":121} -->
 <h3 id="credit">
  Credit
 </h3>
 <p>
  Credits are earned by completing missions and running aviation businesses. You’ll need Credits to get more certifications, purchase new aircraft, establish additional businesses, and cover costs like crew wages or aircraft repairs.
 </p>
 <!-- No repeatable ad for zone: character count repeatable. -->
 <!-- Repeatable debug data: {"injection":"none","adPosition":4,"startingPoint":0,"skipEvery":null,"nbrPlacementFilledEachSkip":4,"nbrPlacementsScanned":4,"ruleCount":1000,"degradationStartingPoint":1,"stopAds":null,"actualCount":354} -->
 <h3 id="exp">
  EXP
 </h3>
 <p>
  Completing missions earns you EXP. The amount of experience points you gain depends on how well you perform, including flight smoothness, take-off and landing efficiency, and safety measures.
 </p>
 <!-- No repeatable ad for zone: character count repeatable. -->
 <!-- Repeatable debug data: {"injection":"none","adPosition":4,"startingPoint":0,"skipEvery":null,"nbrPlacementFilledEachSkip":4,"nbrPlacementsScanned":4,"ruleCount":1000,"degradationStartingPoint":1,"stopAds":null,"actualCount":545} -->
 <h3 id="reputation">
  Reputation
 </h3>
 <p>
  Your performance and attention to detail during missions affect your Reputation. A good Reputation is key to purchasing better aircraft and earning more with your aviation businesses. However, Reputation doesn’t seem to impact the types of missions you receive.
 </p>
