 <p>
  If a
  <em>
   Sekiro
  </em>
  sequel were ever to materialize, a smarter approach to upgrading materials would go a long way. Instead of scattering materials in obscure locations or tying them to random enemy drops, the game could integrate them into structured challenges. For instance, only mini-bosses or specific side quests could yield these materials.
